8. Litigation
-------------

Any litigation relating to this Licence may be brought only in the
courts of a jurisdiction where the defendant maintains its principal
place of business and such litigation shall be governed by laws of that
jurisdiction, without reference to its conflict-of-law provisions.
Nothing in this Section shall prevent a party's ability to bring
cross-claims or counter-claims.

If the defendant is a Contributor, such a litigation relating to this
Licence may be brought only in the courts of a jurisdiction where the
defendant maintained its principal place of business at the point in
time when that Contributor's Contribution was made. Such litigation
shall be governed by laws of that jurisdiction, without reference to
its conflict-of-law provisions.

9. Miscellaneous
----------------

This Licence represents the complete agreement concerning the subject
matter hereof. Except as expressly stated above, You receive no rights
or licences to the intellectual property of any Contributor under this
Licence, whether expressly, by implication or otherwise. All rights in
Covered Software not expressly granted under this Licence are reserved.
No third-party beneficiary rights are created under this Licence.

If any provision of this Licence is held to be
unenforceable, such provision shall be reformed only to the extent
necessary to make it enforceable. Any law or regulation which provides
that the language of a contract shall be construed against the drafter
shall not be used to construe this Licence against a Contributor.

10. Modified Versions
---------------------

If you create software not governed by this Licence, and you want to
create a new licence for such software, you may create and use a
modified version of this Licence if you rename the licence.

Exhibit A - Source Code Form Licence Notice
-------------------------------------------

  This Source Code Form is subject to the terms of the hermACrawler
  Licence. If a copy of the licence was not distributed with this
  file, You have received this Source Code Form in a manner that does
  not comply with the terms of the licence.

If it is not possible or desirable to put the notice in a particular
file, then You may include the notice in a location (such as a LICENSE
file in a relevant directory) where a recipient would be likely to look
for such a notice.